This paper discusses the exploitation of vulnerabilities in BitTorrent to spy on users, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves network infrastructure and data centers, which suggests the sub-categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the identification and profiling of content providers and big downloaders, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) and cryptography and security (cs.CY).
